item.title: CVE-2020-5358|2024-09-17T01:56:50.455Z -- dell -- dell%20encryption%20enterprise
item.description: Dell Encryption versions prior to 10.7 and Dell Endpoint Security Suite versions prior to 2.7 contain a privilege escalation vulnerability due to incorrect permissions. A local malicious user with low privileges could potentially exploit this vulnerability to gain elevated privilege on the affected system with the help of a symbolic link.

item.title: CVE-2020-5385|2024-09-17T02:01:32.478Z -- dell -- dell%20encryption%20enterprise
item.description: Dell Encryption versions prior to 10.8 and Dell Endpoint Security Suite versions prior to 2.8 contain a privilege escalation vulnerability because of an incomplete fix for CVE-2020-5358. A local malicious user with low privileges could potentially exploit this vulnerability to gain elevated privilege on the affected system with the help of a symbolic link.
